). Posterior part covered by tergite I, only most anterior and lateral margins visible from above. Setae of three types : 1 , anteriomedian one cylindrical, blunt, striate; 2 , submedian and anteromarginal ones lanceolate-irregular; 3 , a few lateral ones cylindrical, pointed, with short pubescence or glabrous. Cuticle of head coarse. Only small parts of temporal organs visible from above (
Fig. 47
), organs broadest anteriorly (
Figs 48-49
