Tergites ( Figs 47 , 53– 55 ). All entire, strongly sclerotized, 3 rd (Fig. 53 ) and 4 th ones broadest. Setae in irregular rows, scutellate, inner ones largest. Total number of setae on tergites ( holotype only): I (
